.TH HSH 1 "22 February 2026" "Simple Shell Project" GNU "Shell man page"

.SH NAME
.B hsh
\- small command line shell

.SH SYNOPSIS
Run the program with:
.br
./hsh
.br
After starting, the shell waits for user commands.

.SH DESCRIPTION
hsh is a small Unix-like shell created for learning purposes.
.br
It reads commands from the user, interprets them and executes
programs available on the system.

.br
The shell supports:
.br
- execution of programs with arguments
.br
- built-in commands
.br
- command chaining using ;
.br
- logical operators && and ||
.br
- pipe operations
.br
- environment variable usage
.br
- special variables such as $? and $$

.SH BUILTINS
The shell provides several built-in commands:
.br
exit    terminate the shell
.br
cd      change the current directory
.br
env     display environment variables
.br
help    show help information
.br
history show previously used commands
.br
alias   create command aliases

.SH OPTIONS
Currently this shell does not accept command line options.

.SH EXIT STATUS
Every command returns a status code.
.br
0 indicates success.
.br
Any other value indicates an error.

.SH ENVIRONMENT
The shell works with standard environment variables including:
.br
PATH
.br
$?
.br
$$

.SH EXAMPLES
Interactive mode:
.br
$ ./hsh
.br
$ ls
.br
$ exit

.br
Non-interactive mode:
.br
$ echo "ls" | ./hsh

